    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age ≥ 18 years

          -  1 or more coronary stenoses in the major coronary artery with a vessel diameter ≥ 2mm
             on coronary MR angiogram

          -  Patient who were planned to undergo invasive coronary angiography and fractional flow
             reserve

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  clinically unstable patient

          -  a history of coronary revascularization

          -  infiltrative cardiomyopathy, hypertropic cardiomyopathy, myocarditis

          -  contraindication to use of adenosine

          -  complete occlusion of target lesion
      </textblock>
